PROBLEM STATEMENT 6: Create AN Empty dict Allow four friends to enter their favorite language as value and use keys as their names.Assume that names are unique
d = {}
name = input("Enter friends name :")
lang = input ("Enter the language name:")
d.update({name: lang})
name = input("Enter friends name :")
lang = input ("Enter the language name:")
d.update({name: lang})
name = input("Enter friends name :")
lang = input ("Enter the language name:")
d.update({name: lang})

print(d)
OUTPUT OF THE PROGRAM:Enter friends name :Megha
                      Enter the language name:c
                      Enter friends name :Van
                      Enter the language name:asembly
                      Enter friends name :anay
                      Enter the language name:cpp
                      {'Megha': 'c', 'Van': 'asembly', 'anay': 'cpp'}

PROBLEM STATEMENT 7:If the two friends name are same but language are different
d = {}
name = input("Enter friends name :")
lang = input ("Enter the language name:")
d.update({name: lang})
name = input("Enter friends name :")
lang = input ("Enter the language name:")
d.update({name: lang})
name = input("Enter friends name :")
lang = input ("Enter the language name:")
d.update({name: lang})
name = input("Enter friends name :")
lang = input ("Enter the language name:")
d.update({name: lang})

print(d)
OUTPUT OF THE PROGRAM : Enter friends name :Megha
                        Enter the language name:c
                        Enter friends name :Anny
                        Enter the language name:cpp
                        Enter friends name :rohan
                        Enter the language name:assembly
                        Enter friends name :Anny
                        Enter the language name:python
                        {'Megha': 'c', 'Anny': 'python', 'rohan': 'assembly'}



